            p.
              Welcome!
            p.
              My name is Artur, and I live near Warsaw. I am 41 years old with extensive experience in electromechanics. I have also started my studies in the field of mechatronics. I invite you to visit my website, which is programmer's portfolio.
            p.
              The website features presentations of the most interesting applications I've developed. Each of them  consists of an image (which can be enlarged by clicking on it) and a brief description. Below the graphic, there is a panel providing information about the technology used in the program, including: a link to the source code on the GitHub platform, a link to the website if it's a web application, and a hyperlink to download the program in the case of two games written in C++.
            p.  
              I am an amateur programmer. My dream is to get paid employment in the IT industry, although I am aware that achieving it after forty is challenging. I am self-taught in coding, which can be a tough and tedious challenge at times. Fortunately, tutorials, forums, and ChatGPT make the process easier. Coding forums are an interesting phenomenon, reflecting the will to support of community of programmers. When I couldn't find a solution to a problem someone was facing earlier, I asked a question myself. I received a response within 24 hours, and each time it was useful and, moreover, written in a polite tone. I have come to realize that programmers form a helpful community. Assisting in solving someone else's problem, in my opinion, can be an opportunity to develop skills for the person responding to questions. My path as a self - taught programmer sometimes involved hours of analyzing code, dozens of Google or ChatGPT queries. However, I can proudly say that I never gave up, and I solved every problem independently or with assistance. Programming has definitely taught me, in addition to analytical thinking, perseverance, and consistency in reaching goals.
            p.
	      As an electromechanic, I decided to develop skills in the field of designing automation systems. The first languages I encountered were C++ and LabView. LabView is an incredibly interesting tool. The graphical environment of this language allows the creation of applications for measuring physical quantities, analyzing data, and controlling electronic devices. However, the possibilities of LabView are much greater. For example, I managed to write a game of "Poker" in this language. Creating large projects in the form of block diagrams, however, can be burdened with a lack of transparency in this specific technology. Therefore, I decided to focus on the classical solution – code in the form of plain text. That's why I chose to write my own projects in C++. One undeniable advantage of this language is the readability  of syntax, but since it is a low - level programming tool, mastering memory management skills is necessary to fully utilize its capabilities. I considered it not a good choice for learning a language from the start, so I decided to learn Python. The decision turned out to be appropriate in terms of ease of learning, but the computational efficiency for more complex operations and the limited use of this language in job offers for programmers prompted me to change technologies again. I decided to learn JavaScript, which I considered a compromise between C++ and Python. I believe the decision was correct, especially considering the vast possibilities that the internet provides today. This language is characterized by a large number of ready - made libraries and frameworks, which also determines its positive relationship: accessibility - range of applications. I tie my future to JavaScript, but the path to becoming a fully developed programmer is still far away. I must master asynchronous handling first, and only then begin learning a framework, which will make me a true web developer. 
            p.  
              I am determined to achieve the goal of acquiring programming skills because I love coding. I have always been interested in fields that require creativity and logical thinking skills. When you visit my website, you will surely notice that the majority of projects are games. Electronic entertainment is something that particularly attracts me as a former gamer. Physics engines and artificial intelligence in games now capture my attention as a programmer. The acquired skills of using and combining various technologies enable me to develop future projects in the form of simulators for physical phenomena using machine learning. Feel free to visit my website. 
